<paragraph blockId="90.[151,1436,1890,2023]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
Diagnosis.— 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[298,477,1891,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limae">
<emphasis box="[298,477,1891,1915]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Hypatopa limae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[622,706,1891,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hera">
<emphasis box="[622,706,1891,1915]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">H. hera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[761,862,1892,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arxcis">
<emphasis box="[761,862,1892,1915]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">H. arxcis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in facies but differs from the latter two by having a longer uncus; a more narrowly serrate margin of the proximal flange of the dorsal part of the valva; a longer sclerite of the phallus; and a wider base of the anellus. 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[693,791,1963,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limae">
<emphasis box="[693,791,1963,1987]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">H. limae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has an entire ventroposterior margin of the gnathos that is lacking in 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[344,429,1999,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hera">
<emphasis box="[344,429,1999,2023]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">H. hera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[484,594,2000,2023]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[484,590,2000,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arxcis">H. arxcis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="91.[151,1437,151,1076]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Description.—Head: Vertex and frontoclypeus pale reddish brown. Outer surface of segments 
<number box="[1289,1330,151,175]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
of labial palpus brown intermixed with pale reddish-brown scales, terminal segment pale reddish brown; inner surface pale reddish brown. Antennal scape brown intermixed with pale reddish-brown scales, pecten reddish brown, flagellum brown. Proboscis pale reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="91.[151,1437,151,1076]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Thorax: Tegula with reddish-brown scales tipped with pale reddish brown on basal 
<number box="[1136,1151,295,319]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1161,1174,295,319]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="3.0">3</number>
, pale reddish brown on apical 
<number box="[234,245,332,356]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[257,272,332,356]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="3.0">3</number>
; mesonotum pale reddish brown. Legs brown intermixed with pale reddish-brown scales near midsegments and apical margins of tarsomeres. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[812,911,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 360 – 367" captionStartId="215.[151,264,1932,1955]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,187,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@215.[151,1436,165,1912]" captionTargetPageId="215" captionText="FIGURES 360 – 367. Imagos of Blastobasinae. 360, Hypatopa pica, holotype. 361, Hypatopa hecate, holotype. 362, Hypatopa acus, holotype. 363, Hypatopa crux, holotype. 364, Hypatopa limae, holotype. 365, Hypatopa hera, holotype. 366, Hypatopa arxcis, holotype. 367, Hypatopa caedis, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247458/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Fig. 
<number box="[864,911,367,391]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="364.0">364</number>
</figureCitation>
): Length 10.5 mm (n = 
<number box="[1176,1189,367,391]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="1.0">1</number>
), pale reddish brown; [specimen rubbed]. Undersurface brown. Hindwing: Translucent pale brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="91.[151,1437,151,1076]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Abdomen: Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[537,716,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 153 – 158" captionStartId="178.[151,264,1966,1989]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,196,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@178.[151,1436,193,1945]" captionTargetPageId="178" captionText="FIGURES 153 – 158. Male genitalia of Blastobasinae. 153 – 154, Hypatopa crux (slide 2041). 155 – 156, Hypatopa limae (slide 2691). 157 – 158, Hypatopa hera (slide 2667)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247420/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Figs. 
<number box="[613,716,439,463]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="155.5" valueMax="156.0" valueMin="155.0">155–156</number>
</figureCitation>
): Uncus gradually narrowed from widened base, slightly downcurved, narrowly rounded apically, sparsely setose, length about equal to width of anal opening. Gnathos narrow, confluent with tegumen, ventroposterior margin slightly protuberant mesially, forming slightly raised lobe. Sockets of tergal setae not extending beyond midlength of tegumen. Valva divided; ventral part basally protracted inwardly, gradually widened near middle, abruptly narrowed apically, forming inwardly curved, spinelike process; process acutely curved near 
<number box="[469,479,620,644]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[491,507,620,644]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="2.0">2</number>
, setose on outer margin, planate on inner surface; ventral margin slightly upturned beyond middle, forming narrow fold to near setose lobe at base of apical process; dorsal part with apical portion of costa extending dorsally, forming setose digitate process; process broadly curved inwardly; basal ridge of digitate process extending ventrally fusing dorsally with proximal flange; flange ellipsoid, bearing sparse microtrichiae on upper 
<number box="[225,235,764,788]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[246,263,764,788]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="4.0">4</number>
, densely packed spinelike setae on lower 
<number box="[753,766,764,788]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[777,793,764,788]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="4.0">4</number>
; margin serrate. Juxta bandlike. Vinculum semicircular. Phallus and sclerite of phallus longer than valva; phallus straight, bulbous basally, sclerite of phallus sigmoidshaped; anellus bearing two elongate setal clusters on ventrolateral surface. Female Genitalia: Unknown.
</paragraph>
